The paper focuses on improving the speed and efficiency of data decompression, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of GPUs and SIMD architectures also suggests a connection to Computer Architecture (cs.AR). The sacrifice of compression efficiency for increased parallelism may also relate to the field of Computational Complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper discusses energy savings, which could be relevant to Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
